value.0: The sea is a savage place, and those that travel it had best be willing to pay the price of challenging Umberlee's domain. All should know the Bitch Queen and fear her, for the wind and the wave can reach everywhere if sufficiently angered. Fair offerings bring fair winds to sea travelers, but those that do not pay their respects will find that the sea is as cold as Umberlee's heart. Spread the word of the might of Umberlee, and let no service be done in her name without a price. Make folk hear the wind and wave unless a cleric of Umberlee is there to protect them. Slay those who ascribe sea and shore storms to Talos.

Value.value: The icy depths begin to overwhelm your body, chilling you to the bone and causing you to feel as though you were being burned by ice...

value.0: Before you stands a heavily weathered idol of Umberlee.  It appears that even her worshippers have the ability to get on her bad side, given that this temple at the bottom of the sea.

Despite being submerged long enough for sealife to partially take over the citadel's halls, the structure of the building appears in relatively remarkable shape, however that will likely change in a few more short decades.
Though there appears to have been some sort of cave-in, there seems to be more to this citadel below...
